&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a well-funded biotech company that is redefining drug discovery and development through our fully integrated platform. We combine ultra-high-throughput microfluidics driven functional screening, computational engineering, and translational immunology into a unified engine. Rather than approaching drug development as a series of disconnected steps, we seamlessly integrate the discovery of novel targets, functional screening of binders, computational optimization, and predictive safety assessment to develop more better and safer therapeutics. This end-to-end approach enables faster iteration, deeper biological insight, and the development of better drugs with greater precision and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Chief Executive Officer, the CSO/VP of Research is an accomplished scientific leader, who can professionally and effectively execute the research initiatives towards Shennon Bio’s vision and strategy. This role will lead the R&amp;amp;D function on the therapeutics side and play a critical part in developing biopharma partnerships. An ideal candidate will be an R&amp;amp;D leader with a passion for immunotherapy and knows how to bring TCE candidates into the clinic.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This person will maintain professional and productive relationships with internal colleagues and external collaborators with an entrepreneurial &amp;amp; go-to-market mindset. Shennon Bio’s vision of this candidate is an organized leader that has a self-starter attitude and a strong background in immune-oncology and TCE development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the CEO and various advisors to scale and refine the pipeline for both external partnerships and in-house therapeutic programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the R&amp;amp;D team to refine the pipeline and drive lead candidates forward.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish a strategic roadmap and present key data-driven insights to the CEO and the board.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead efforts to scale the organization in the way of scientific talent, and capital equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish &amp;amp; maintain new relationships with external collaborators such as targeted clinicians, biotech and pharma leadership, and key opinion leaders in the field of immuno-oncology and immunotherapy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize strategic communications with the internal team and exernal partners, tailored specifically to Shennon’s growth strategy and vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote strong scientific excellence and foster an open culture of ideation, innovation, and deep scientific rigor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications and Experience: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ph.D. in a field related to immuno-oncology and 10+ years of industry experience in designing, managing, and leading R&amp;amp;D programs required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Domain Expertise in immuno-oncology and TCEs.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep Expertise in directing TCE programs into the clinic.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability in directing pre-clinical assets to successful IND and clinical trials&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pre-established relationships with pharma companies and partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in scaling a pre-clinical company to commercial success with capital efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to plan decisions with discipline and possess an entrepreneurial mindset.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to present clearly and concisely to the executive team, board members, and external stakeholders as a thought leader and trusted advisor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Articulate and thoughtful communicator who effectively communicates across all levels of the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal

&lt;p&gt;Shennon Biotechnologies is a well-funded early-stage startup based in San Francisco that has created a proprietary single cell platform for the development of more effective cancer immunotherapies. We are driven by a commitment to excellence and are always on the lookout for passionate, curious, and talented individuals to join our team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Shennon, we understand that the perfect opportunity may not always be available. If you’re excited to work with us but don’t see a current position that matches your skills, we invite you to submit your resume for future opportunities. While we may not have any immediate openings, we believe in proactively building a talent pool to draw from when positions become available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By expressing your interest now, you’ll be among the first to know when relevant opportunities arise. We value the diversity of talent and ideas, and we’re always excited to connect with passionate professionals who share our vision. Joining our talent pool ensures that when the right opportunity emerges, you’ll be at the forefront of our minds.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong commitment to Shennon’s key values: collaboration, ownership, and authenticity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience in your field of expertise and a deep interest in contributing to the innovative and impactful work we do at Shennon&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Available for full-time work onsite at our office in San Francisco, CA.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How to Apply:&lt;/strong&gt; Please submit your resume along with a cover letter detailing how you believe you would fit into the Shennon team, now or in the future. We will keep your information on file and reach out when a suitable position becomes available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equal Opportunity Employer:&lt;/strong&gt; Shennon is an equal opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are a well-funded biotech company that is redefining drug discovery and development through our fully integrated platform. We combine ultra-high-throughput microfluidics driven functional screening, computational engineering, and translational immunology into a unified engine. Rather than approaching drug development as a series of disconnected steps, we seamlessly integrate the discovery of novel targets, functional screening of binders, computational optimization, and predictive safety assessment to develop more better and safer therapeutics. This end-to-end approach enables faster iteration, deeper biological insight, and the development of better drugs with greater precision and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for a research associate to join our interdisciplinary team. The candidate is expected to adapt quickly and communicate well, especially in a fast-paced startup environment. We pay competitive salaries with bonus and equity, plus full benefits that include medical, dental, vision, 401k match, commuter benefits and daily lunch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carry out a variety of cell biology tasks, including mammalian cell culture, virus harvesting, and transfections/transduction of various cell lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Isolate and engineer primary T cells using different techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform functional assays to evaluate T cell responses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with molecular cloning tasks including design, PCR, gel extraction, transformation, plasmid preparation, and sequence analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with team on other experiments when needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Molecular Biology, Cell Biology, Biochemistry, Biomedical Engineering or equivalent.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Skill sets required: molecular cloning, flow cytometry, ELISA, cell line and primary T cell culture, and lentiviral transduction.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;2+ years of industry experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Responsible, accountable, and detail-oriented&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Detail oriented, excellent organization skills and communication skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nice to haves:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of T cell immunology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with TCE development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with NGS sequencing and analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shennon Bio is an equal opportunity employer, and we welcome applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Type: &lt;/strong&gt;Full-time, Mon-Fri&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;: Daily lunch + Commuter benefits + Health insurance (Medical, Dental and Vision, 100% premium covered for Gold plan) + life insurance, flexible time off and sick leave, unlimited healthy snacks and drinks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Company Culture: &lt;/strong&gt;Collaboration, Ownership and Authenticity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are a well-funded biotech company that is redefining biologics discovery and development through our fully integrated platform. We combine ultra-high-throughput microfluidics driven functional screening, computational engineering, and translational immunology into a unified engine. Rather than approaching biologics development as a series of disconnected steps, we seamlessly integrate the discovery of novel targets, functional screening of binders, computational optimization, and predictive safety assessment to develop more better and safer therapeutics. This end-to-end approach enables faster iteration, deeper biological insight, and the development of better TCEs with greater precision and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking for an antibody development scientist to join our interdisciplinary team. The candidate is expected to adapt quickly and communicate well, especially in a fast-paced startup environment. They will collaborate with other team members and be part of an exciting journey. We pay competitive salaries with bonus and equity, plus full benefits that include medical, dental, vision, 401k match, commuter benefits and daily lunch.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design T-cell engagers and execute their development and optimization campaigns.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with internal and external team on antibody discovery, characterization, and production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive developability and manufacturability assessments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage external relationships and deliverables.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with computational scientists and immunologists to optimize and validate candidate molecules through iterative engineering and in vitro/in vivo studies.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD degree in Biochemistry, Protein engineering, Bioengineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong background in biochemistry, protein engineering, and Molecular Biology.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;2+ years industry experience&lt;/strong&gt; leading the design, production, and developability optimization of multi-specific antibodies.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with antibody discovery/engineering using phage/yeast display is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with in vitro functional studies of multi-specific antibodies is a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with CROs is plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to work in a fast-paced startup environment, take initiative, and drive projects forward independently.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compensation and Benefits:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Compensation:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$120,000 - $160,000 (depending on the depth of expertise) + 4% 401K match + 10% performance bonus + equity.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will also consider a Principal Scientist with proven technical expertise plus cross-functional project leadership. Compensation will be adjusted accordingly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Benefits:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Daily lunches; Commuter Benefits; Unlimited snacks and drinks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medical, Dental, Vision; 100% Premium Covered.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Disability Insurance, Life Insurance; Workplace Insurance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are a well-funded biotech company that is redefining drug discovery and development through our fully integrated platform. We combine ultra-high-throughput microfluidics driven functional screening, computational engineering, and translational immunology into a unified engine. Rather than approaching drug development as a series of disconnected steps, we seamlessly integrate the discovery of novel targets, functional screening of binders, computational optimization, and predictive safety assessment to develop more better and safer therapeutics. This end-to-end approach enables faster iteration, deeper biological insight, and the development of better drugs with greater precision and confidence.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Summer Intern who will support project-based analytical work for executive leadership and cross-functional scientific teams. This role will contribute to generating insights related to oncology and autoimmune therapeutics, competitive landscapes, emerging technologies, market opportunities, and broader industry trends that help inform strategic decision-making. The intern will collaborate closely with leadership and scientific teams to contribute to targeted analyses, strategic assessments, and decision-support materials. The ideal candidate has exposure to or a strong interest in biotechnology, business strategy, market research, and understanding how scientific and commercial insights intersect in the development of innovative therapeutics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are open to both part-time and full-time candidates. For part-time candidates, we are open to engagement past the summer depending on business needs.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Gain:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct exposure to executive-level strategic decision-making within an early-stage biotech company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience evaluating oncology and autoimmune therapeutic landscapes, competitive dynamics, and emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The opportunity to work closely with leadership, scientific and business advisors, scientists, and engineers building next-generation immunotherapy platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience at the intersection of biotech strategy, market intelligence, and scientific innovation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exposure to how early-stage biotech companies evaluate pipeline opportunities, partnerships, platform positioning, and long-term growth strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A high-impact internship experience with broad visibility across scientific and business functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct market research and competitive landscape analyses across oncology and autoimmune therapeutic areas.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze current standards of care, approved therapeutics, clinical-stage pipelines, emerging treatment modalities and patient population triage, as well as biotech and pharmaceutical company activity, including partnerships, licensing, financings, acquisitions, and clinical milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support strategic assessments of oncology targets, immunology pathways, and emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop presentations, market maps, executive summaries, and reports for internal and external stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help executive team optimize pitch decks for external business conversations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate cross-functionally with scientific and leadership teams on strategic and market intelligence projects.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills and Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Currently pursuing a PhD/MBA degree, with a focus in healthcare and/or biotechnology. Ideally someone with a PhD in immuno-oncology who is interested in business and has some business training.&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/
